title: Lung Cancer 2T
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA from the tissue specimens were isolated using TRIzol® reagent (Invitrogen, Calsbad, CA) and purified with RNeasy® mini kits (Qiagen) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: The IVT reaction was carried out in the presence of T7 RNA Polymerase and a biotinylated nucleotide analog/ribonucleotide mix for complementary RNA (cRNA) amplification and biotin labeling.
hyb_protocol: The biotinylated cRNA targets were then cleaned up, fragmented, and hybridized to GeneChip® Human Genome U133 Plus 2.0 expression arrays (Affymetrix, Inc., Santa Clara, CA).  After 16 hours of hybridization at 45 °C, the arrays were washed by Fluidics Station 450
scan_protocol: Chips were scanned using the GeneChip Scanner 3000
data_processing: Background-adjusted signals were normalized by three steps: Robust Multichip Analysis (RMA), median polish method, and quantile normalization algorithm.
contact_department: Department of Public Health, Institute of Epidemiology and Preventive Medicine
